(-)-P7C3-S243 did not show significant toxicity towards 3 human cancer cell lines tested (IC50 > 10 μΜ vs H2122, H2009 and HCC44).
Several cytochrome P450's were insensitive to (-)-P7C3-S243 (3A4, 2C9, 3D6, 2C8, 2B6) while CYP1A2 and CYP2C19 showed modest IC50 values of 20 and 1.9 μΜ, respectively.
Of 47 neuronal receptors and channels tested, only the μ-opioid receptor (IC50 = 8.2 μΜ) and the peripheral benzodiazepine receptor (also known as translocator protein, TSPO, IC50 = 0.35 μΜ) showed any ligand displacement.
Moreover, while we see enantiomeric specificity in the neurogenesis (FIG. 2) and MPTP assays (FIG. 3), both enantiomers of P7C3-S243 bind TSPO with similarly weak affinity (0.35 and 0.68 μΜ).
